```julia
function timezone_bumper(dt::DateTime, bump::Integer = 3)
    if isa(dt, Date)
        error("timezone_bumper can only operate on DateTime types, not Date types.")
    end
    return DateTime(Dates.value(dt) + Dates.hour(bump))
end
```

This function checks if the input `dt` is a `Date` type and throws an error if it is. If `dt` is a `DateTime`, it increments the time by `bump` hours using `Dates.value` and `Dates.hour` to perform the actual addition. The default value for `bump` is set to 3 hours.
